                <note rend="inline" type="source">123C38/108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-13T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 10th noon.</p>
                <p>Department knows of no tug proceeding to Costa Rica. Endeavor to get telegram
                    through to Consul Chase inquiring as to his safety <pb facs="0920" n="818"
                        xml:id="pg_818"/> and welfare. Cable Department fullest possible news
                    regarding Acosta’s expedition and again warn [?] authorities in Nicaragua to see
                    there is no just cause of complaint on part of Costa Rica.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
